  <div class="post"><a name="113823933194588017"></a>
         
    <h3 class="post-title">
	 
	 Clean Up Your Digital Dirt
	 
    </h3>
    

	         <div class="post-body">
	<div>
      <div style="clear:both;"></div><a href="http://www.careerjournal.com">The Wall Street Journal Career Site</a> is running an article title <a href="http://www.careerjournal.com/jobhunting/usingnet/20060112-flesher.html">How to Clean Up Your Digital Dirt Before it Trashes Your Job Search</a>. Here are some excerpts:<br /><br /><span style="font-style: italic;">"</span><span style="font-style: italic;" class="articleContent">Unflattering personal information drifting around the Internet, known by some  as 'digital dirt,' can doom a job search before it even gets started. Job  hunters should know that recruiters can, and often do, read much of what's  posted about them on the Web.</span><span style="font-style: italic;">"</span><br /><br /><span style="font-style: italic;">"</span><span style="font-style: italic;" class="articleContent">Search engines might not find your risqué profile on social-networking sites  like Facebook.com, but that doesn't mean it's hidden from recruiters. Chris  Hughes, a spokesman for Facebook, says he's heard that recruiters with alumni  email addresses log in to look up job candidates who attended the same school.</span><span style="font-style: italic;">"</span><div style="clear:both; padding-bottom:0.25em"></div>
    </div>
    </div>
    
    <p class="post-footer">
      <em>posted by Robert R. Peterson at <a href="http://landingthejob.blogspot.com/2006/01/clean-up-your-digital-dirt.html" title="permanent link">5:33 PM</a></em>
      

         <a class="comment-link" href="https://www.blogger.com/comment.g?blogID=19439216&postID=113823933194588017">7 comments</a>

      
<a class="comment-link" href="http://landingthejob.blogspot.com/2006/01/clean-up-your-digital-dirt.html#links">links to this post</a>

  <span class="item-action"><a href="http://www.blogger.com/email-post.g?blogID=19439216&postID=113823933194588017" title="Email Post"><img class="icon-action" alt="" src="http://img2.blogblog.com/img/icon18_email.gif" height="13" width="18"/></a></span>
    </p>
  
